# GitHub Credentials File Example
# Copy this to ~/.config/github/credentials and update with your actual credentials
# Make sure to set appropriate permissions: chmod 600 ~/.config/github/credentials

GITHUB_USERNAME=your_github_username
GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# Token Permissions Required:
# - repo: To clone and read repository contents
# - read:user: To access user information (if needed)
#
# To create a Personal Access Token:
# 1. Go to GitHub → Settings → Developer settings → Personal access tokens
# 2. Create a new token with the required scopes
# 3. Copy the token value and paste it above
